## Work Environment

### Datascience Workspace (`~/workspace/git/datascience/`)

Contains **4 separate git repos**, not a monorepo:

| Repo | Path | Default Branch | Workflow | Purpose |
|------|------|----------------|----------|---------|
| **datascience** | `datascience/datascience/` | `master` | Branch/MR | Source code, Dockerfiles, CI jobs |
| **helm_charts** | `datascience/helm_charts/` | `main` | Branch/MR | Helm chart templates |
| **config** | `datascience/config/` | `main` | Trunk-based | ArgoCD deployment config (values files) |
| **infrastructure** | `datascience/infrastructure/` | `main` | Trunk-based | Terraform (AWS, ECR, EKS) |

### AWS & Kubernetes
- SSO: `aws sso login --sso-session KN-Operations`
- Profiles: `dev`, `prod`
- Sync kubectl: `update_kubectl`
- Pod log retention is very short (minutes to ~1 hour due to kubelet rotation) ‚Äî for historical logs, query Loki instead

### Observability (Grafana/Loki)
- **Architecture**: Grafana Alloy collectors (in `monitoring` ns) ‚Üí centralized Loki ‚Üí centralized Grafana
- **Grafana (dev)**: `grafana.nonprod.example.com` ‚Äî `apps-dev-cluster`
- **Grafana (prod)**: `grafana.prod.example.com` ‚Äî `apps-prod-cluster`
- **Querying logs via CLI**: Use Grafana session cookie (no K8s access needed). `export GRAFANA_SESSION_DEV=<cookie>` / `GRAFANA_SESSION_PROD=<cookie>`. Get cookie: browser DevTools ‚Üí Application ‚Üí Cookies ‚Üí `grafana_session`. Query via `/api/datasources/proxy/<id>/loki/api/v1/query_range` (POST with `--data-urlencode`). Default datascience datasource: `aie-grafana-loki` (id 221 on dev).
- **Direct Loki auth**: OAuth2 client credentials from `monitoring/alloy-oauth2-credentials` K8s secret. Token endpoint is AWS Cognito ‚Äî only `client_credentials` grant supported, no personal user CLI auth.
- **Tenant/cluster mapping**: Check the Alloy configmap in `monitoring` ns for `tenant_id` and `external_labels`

### Jira
- `jira` CLI on PATH ‚Äî prefer over REST API. Auth: `export JIRA_API_TOKEN=$(bw_get_secret "Jira API Token")`
- **Default project:** `AI` (AI and Data Science) ‚Äî **always add label `AIE`** on tickets
- **Always ask** which epic to attach the ticket to (if applicable)
- **Formatting gotcha:** `jira issue create -b`/`-T` mangles Jira wiki markup (escapes special chars, converts `#` lists to `h1.`). Workaround: create ticket with CLI, then update description via REST API: `curl -X PUT -H "Authorization: Bearer $JIRA_API_TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @body.json "https://jira.example.com/rest/api/2/issue/{KEY}"`
- **Always invoke the `working-with-jira` skill** before doing any Jira operations
- Full CLI/REST reference in `working-with-jira` skill (kn-internal-tools plugin)

### Confluence (wiki.example.com)
- REST API + `mark` CLI. Auth: `bw_get_secret "Confluence API Token"` (separate from Jira PAT)
- Full reference in `working-with-confluence` skill (kn-internal-tools plugin)

### Chezmoi (Dotfiles)
- Home dir files managed by chezmoi. **Never edit template targets directly** (`~/CLAUDE.md`, `~/.claude/settings.json`)
- Full workflow in `editing-dotfiles-with-chezmoi` skill (`~/.claude/skills/`)
- `chezmoi forget` needs `--force` in non-interactive shells (no TTY for confirmation)
- Autocommit only fires on `chezmoi add`/`re-add` ‚Äî direct source edits need manual `git -C ~/.local/share/chezmoi` commit
- **Go template whitespace**: `{{ "{{" }}- if }}` (left-dash) trims before ‚Äî preserves indentation of next line. `{{ "{{" }} if -}}` (right-dash) trims after ‚Äî use for block-level conditionals. Inline for single values: `{{ "{{" }} if .x }}val1{{ "{{" }} else }}val2{{ "{{" }} end }}`

{{ if eq .chezmoi.os "darwin" }}
### macOS Config Paths
- lazygit/k9s use `~/Library/Application Support/` on macOS, `~/.config/` on Linux
- lazygit follows symlinks; **k9s does NOT** (uses `lstat`) ‚Äî needs real files at native path
- k9s per-cluster skins fully override global skin (no inheritance) ‚Äî per-cluster skins must include the full theme
- Cross-platform chezmoi strategy: `.chezmoiignore` with OS conditionals for k9s; symlink script for lazygit
- Time Machine local snapshots: `/Volumes/com.apple.TimeMachine.localsnapshots/Backups.backupdb/`
